-- MasterCard profit jumps 15.5 pct as card usage rises
-- By Amrutha Gayathri in Bangalore
-- Thu Oct 30, 2014 08:09AM EDT
-- None



Oct 30 (Reuters) - MasterCard Inc <MA.N>, the world's second-largest debit and credit card company, posted a 15.5 percent rise in quarterly profit as more customers used its cards to make purchases.

The company's net income rose to $1.02 billion, or 87 cents per share, in the third quarter ended Sept. 30 from $879 million, or 73 cents per share, a year earlier. [ID:nBwb53Htma] Net revenue rose 12.8 percent to $2.5 billion.